.TH NHOPKG-OVERLAY 8 "@RELEASEDATE@" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "Nhopkg Manual"
.SH NAME
nhopkg-overlay \- set up an isolated overlay filesystem for building packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nhopkg-overlay
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBnhopkg-overlay\fR creates an isolated overlay filesystem environment for
building nhopkg packages. It takes no command-line arguments.
.P
It sets up an overlay filesystem at \fI/var/lib/nhopkg-overlay/\fR with:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
\fIlowerdir=\fR (host root filesystem)
.IP \(bu 4
\fIupperdir=/var/lib/nhopkg-overlay/upper\fR
.IP \(bu 4
\fIworkdir=/var/lib/nhopkg-overlay/work\fR
.IP \(bu 4
Mount point: \fI/var/lib/nhopkg-overlay/root\fR
.RE
.P
The following directories are bind-mounted into the overlay:
.RS
.IP \(bu 4
\fI/dev\fR, \fI/proc\fR, \fI/sys\fR, \fI/run\fR
.IP \(bu 4
The current working directory at \fI/work\fR
.RE
.P
After setup, it drops into a \fBchroot\fR at the overlay root, providing an
isolated build environment. All changes are written to the upper layer and
do not affect the host system.
.P
On exit (EXIT, INT, TERM signals), it recursively unmounts everything and
removes \fI/var/lib/nhopkg-overlay/\fR.
.P
Must be run as root.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start an overlay build environment
.B sudo nhopkg-overlay
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nhopkg (8),
.BR nhopkg.conf (5),
.BR nhopkg-src (8),
.BR chroot (8),
.BR mount (8)
.SH AUTHOR
